[SN]TITLE[SN]
Truro acid attack: Man denies charge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man accused of carrying out an acid attack in Cornwall has denied carrying out the assault.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Businessman Andreas Christopheros, 29, was critically injured in the attack on his doorstep last December in Truro.
He suffered severe facial wounds and damage to his sight.
At Truro Crown Court, David Phillips, 48, from Hastings, East Sussex, denied causing grievous bodily harm with intent and is expected to go on trial on 8 June.
